4. O testimonium animae. Gomp. de test. anim. 1, ‘ Novum testi- monium advoco . . . consiste in medio, anima,’ etc.; de coron. 63 de reS. carn. 3. This is a very memorable argument, characteristic of Tertul- lian’s school of apology, drawn from the inner depths of conscious moral being. The peculiar aim of Tei-tullian is to ennoble the simple human conscience, and at the same time to discard all extraneous mental culture.
